a server is a physical machine that host a webserver
the domain name is for accessing the web server
the DNS record www stores the ip address ofthe server
the web server isolates what you want people to acces from everything else on the server
the role of the application server is to handle the apllication and its database referencing
the database stores data to be used in the application
the webserver contains a html index page to allow for the user to interract with the application
SPOF stands for single point of failure and the spof with this webserver design is if the server needed to be updated either hardware or software
downtime is however long it takes to get the main server back up
and its limited to the hardware available to it
